translated: Friden, Axel Vilhelm, physician, Västervik, b. 26/5/02 in Nässjö to director F.J.F. and N.S. Krantz. Married in 1934 to Stina Samuelsson. Children: Staffan b. 1944, Eva-Ohristina b. 1945. Passed matriculation exam in Jönköping in 1921, became a medical candidate in Stockholm in 1925, and received a medical license there in 1929. Worked as an assistant physician at the surgical department of the Jönköping hospital in 1927, acting chief medical officer in the Tärna district and at the prison infirmary there in 1929, an assistant physician at the Mariestad hospital, and as an assistant physician and acting junior physician at Söderköping hospital in 1930. Served as a physician on the Swedish America Line ship Kungsbolm in 1931. Established a medical practice in Södertälje in 1932, and in Västervik starting in 1933, where he became acting chief city physician in 1934-35, school physician at Västervik secondary school since 1934, and physician for post and telegraph department since 1934. Worked as a school physician at Västervik elementary school since 1937 and a physician for Ankarsrum estate since 1937. Started a child welfare center in Västervik in 1935.
